 <h2 class="text-lg font-black uppercase mb-4">What is a GaN Charger? (The Science Simplified)</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-300">Gallium nitride (GaN) is a compound semiconductor that replaces traditional silicon in chargers. It offers superior <strong>energy efficiency</strong>, smaller size, and less heat generation through <strong>high-frequency switching</strong> and better <strong>heat dissipation</strong>.</p>
 <div class="mt-6 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
 <div class="bg-white/10 rounded-lg p-4">
 <h3 class="font-bold mb-2">Bandgap Advantage</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-300">GaN has 3.4 eV bandgap vs silicon's 1.1 eV,, allowing higher voltage handling without breakdown.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-white/10 rounded-lg p-4">
 <h3 class="font-bold mb-2">Electron Mobility</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-300">GaN electrons move 30% faster than silicon, enabling faster charging with less energy loss.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>
 <section id="benefits" class="mb-16">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">1. What Are the Key Benefits of GaN Technology?</h2>
 <div class="bg-brandBlue/5 border-l-4 border-brandOrange p-5 rounded-r-xl mb-8">
 <p class="text-[11px] font-black text-brandOrange uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">QUICK ANSWER</p>
 <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">GaN (Gallium Nitride) chargers reach 95%+ power conversion efficiency versus 85% for silicon, run measurably cooler, and pack the same wattage into a 30-50% smaller body. For OEM/ODM brands, this translates to lower shipping costs, lower return rates from heat-related failures, and a clear premium-product story for retail.</p>
 </div>
