 <section id="adoption-timeline" class="mb-16">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">8. GaN Adoption Timeline</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6">The consumer electronics industry has embraced GaN technology through distinct phases. Here's the evolution that brought us to today's advanced GaN chargers.</p>
 <div class="space-y-6">
 <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
 <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
 <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-brandBlue rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-black text-sm">2019</div>
 <div class="w-0.5 h-16 bg-slate-200 mt-2"></div>
 </div>
 <div class="pb-6">
 <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">First Consumer GaN Chargers</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Anker and AUKEY release the first generation of consumer GaN chargers. These early products were limited to 30-45W and carried premium pricing. Market reception was cautiously optimistic as consumers experienced the size benefits firsthand.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
 <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
 <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-brandBlue rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-black text-sm">2020</div>
 <div class="w-0.5 h-16 bg-slate-200 mt-2"></div>
 </div>
 <div class="pb-6">
 <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">65W Becomes Standard</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">The 65W GaN charger emerges as the sweet spot for laptop charging. Multiple manufacturers release competing products, driving prices down. GaN charging becomes synonymous with "fast charging" in consumer marketing.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
 <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
 <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-brandBlue rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-black text-sm">2021</div>
 <div class="w-0.5 h-16 bg-slate-200 mt-2"></div>
 </div>
 <div class="pb-6">
 <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Multi-Port Revolution</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">GaN chargers with 2-4 ports become mainstream. The efficiency gains allow multiple-device charging without overheating. Companies like <a href="https://www.wowohcool.com" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange">WOWOHCOOL</a> begin offering <a href="/products/gan-charger" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange">custom GaN solutions</a> for B2B clients.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
 <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
 <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-brandBlue rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-black text-sm">2022</div>
 <div class="w-0.5 h-16 bg-slate-200 mt-2"></div>
 </div>
 <div class="pb-6">
 <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">100W+ Goes Mainstream</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">100W and 140W GaN chargers hit the market, capable of powering high-performance laptops and workstations. Apple adopts GaN for their 140W MacBook Pro charger, lending credibility to the technology.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
 <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
 <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-brandBlue rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-black text-sm">2023-24</div>
 <div class="w-0.5 h-16 bg-slate-200 mt-2"></div>
 </div>
 <div class="pb-6">
 <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Market Maturation</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">GaN charger prices drop to near-silicon levels for mainstream products. Integration of GaN chips into power strips, travel adapters, and automotive chargers expands the market. The technology becomes the default choice for new charging product development.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
 <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
 <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-brandOrange rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-black text-sm">2025+</div>
 </div>
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Next Generation: 150W-240W</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm"> Manufacturers are developing chargers exceeding 150W for gaming laptops and power-hungry devices. GaN technology continues to evolve toward higher power densities, smaller form factors, and lower price points.</p>
 </div>
