 </svg>Material Efficiency</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">GaN's smaller size means less raw material consumption in manufacturing. The compact designs require fewer components, reducing electronic waste and shipping emissions. According to <a href="https://www.yolegroup.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange">Yole Group</a>, GaN technology in power applications could save 2-3 million tons of CO2 annually by 2027.</p>
