 <section id="sourcing" class="mb-16">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">9. Sourcing GaN Chargers from China</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6">China remains the global manufacturing hub for GaN chargers, with over 80% of world production concentrated in the Pearl River Delta. Understanding the sourcing landscape helps B2B buyers make strategic decisions about supplier selection and certification requirements.</p>
 <div class="space-y-6">
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
 <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3"><svg class="icon-industry mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 512 512">
 <path d="M32 32C14.3 32 0 46.3 0 64L0 432c0 26.5 21.5 48 48 48l416 0c26.5 0 48-21.5 48-48l0-279.8c0-18.2-19.4-29.7-35.4-21.1l-156.6 84.3 0-63.2c0-18.2-19.4-29.7-35.4-21.1L128 215.4 128 64c0-17.7-14.3-32-32-32L32 32z" fill="currentColor"/>
 </svg>Manufacturing Ecosystem</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Shenzhen and Dongguan host a comprehensive supply chain for GaN charger manufacturing, from semiconductor fabs to final assembly. This concentration enables competitive pricing and rapid prototype-to-production timelines — typically 4-6 weeks for custom designs.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
 <h4 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3"><svg class="icon-certificate mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 576 512">
 <path d="M239.2-8c-6.1-6.2-15-8.7-23.4-6.4S200.9-5.6 198.8 2.8L183.5 63c-1.1 4.4-5.6 7-9.9 5.7L113.8 51.9c-8.4-2.4-17.4 0-23.5 6.1s-8.5 15.1-6.1 23.5l16.9 59.8c1.2 4.3-1.4 8.8-5.7 9.9L35.1 166.5c-8.4 2.1-15 8.7-17.3 17.1s.2 17.3 6.4 23.4l44.5 43.3c3.2 3.1 3.2 8.3 0 11.5L24.3 305.1c-6.2 6.1-8.7 15-6.4 23.4s8.9 14.9 17.3 17.1l60.2 15.3c4.4 1.1 7 5.6 5.7 9.9L84.2 430.5c-2.4 8.4 0 17.4 6.1 23.5s15.1 8.5 23.5 6.1l59.8-16.9c4.3-1.2 8.8 1.4 9.9 5.7l15.3 60.2c2.1 8.4 8.7 15 17.1 17.3s17.3-.2 23.4-6.4l43.3-44.5c3.1-3.2 8.3-3.2 11.5 0L337.3 520c6.1 6.2 15 8.7 23.4 6.4s14.9-8.9 17.1-17.3L393.1 449c1.1-4.4 5.6-7 9.9-5.7l59.8 16.9c8.4 2.4 17.4 0 23.5-6.1s8.5-15.1 6.1-23.5l-16.9-59.8c-1.2-4.3 1.4-8.8 5.7-9.9l60.2-15.3c8.4-2.1 15-8.7 17.3-17.1s-.2-17.4-6.4-23.4l-44.5-43.3c-3.2-3.1-3.2-8.3 0-11.5l44.5-43.3c6.2-6.1 8.7-15 6.4-23.4s-8.9-14.9-17.3-17.1l-60.2-15.3c-4.4-1.1-7-5.6-5.7-9.9l16.9-59.8c2.4-8.4 0-17.4-6.1-23.5s-15.1-8.5-23.5-6.1L403 68.8c-4.3 1.2-8.8-1.4-9.9-5.7L377.8 2.8c-2.1-8.4-8.7-15-17.1-17.3s-17.3.2-23.4 6.4L294 36.5c-3.1 3.2-8.3 3.2-11.5 0L239.2-8z" fill="currentColor"/>
 </svg>Quality Certification Requirements</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Ensure your supplier provides: CE, FCC, RoHS, and UL certifications. For European market access, mandatory CE marking applies. The <a href="https://ec.europa.eu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange">EU CE marking documentation</a> should be verified with the supplier. Always request test reports from accredited laboratories.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
 <h4 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3"><svg class="icon-handshake mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 576 512">
 <path d="M268.9 85.2L152.3 214.8c-4.6 5.1-4.4 13.5 17.9 30.5 30.5 80 30.5 110.5 0l31.8-31.8c4.2-4.2 9.5-6.5 14.9-6.9 6.8-.6 13.8 1.7 19 6.9L505.6 376 576 320 576 32 464 96 440.2 80.1C424.4 69.6 405.9 64 386.9 64l-70.4 0c-1.1 0-2.3 0-3.4.1-16.9.9-32.8 8.5-44.2 21.1zM116.6 182.7L223.4 64 183.8 64c-25.5 0-49.9 10.1-67.9 28.1L112 96 0 32 0 320 156.4 450.3c23 19.2 52 29.7 81.9 29.7l15.7 0-7-7c-9.4-9.4-9.4-24.6 0-33.9s24.6-9.4 33.9 0l41 41 9 0c19.1 0 37.8-4.3 54.8-12.3L359 441c-9.4-9.4-9.4-24.6 0-33.9s24.6-9.4 33.9 0l32 32 17.5-17.5c8.9-8.9 11.5-21.8 7.6-33.1l-137.9-136.8-14.9 14.9c-49.3 49.3-129.1 49.3-178.4 0-23-23-23.9-59.9-2.2-84z" fill="currentColor"/>
 </svg>Working with Factories</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Direct factory partnerships yield 20-40% cost savings versus trading companies. Key considerations: minimum order quantities (typically 500-1000 units), tooling costs for custom molds, and payment terms (commonly 30% advance, 70% before shipping). Our <a href="/service" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange">OEM/ODM services</a> streamline this process.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
 <h4 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3"><svg class="icon-vial mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 512 512">
